<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
Alternate term for <a title="Deflection" href="Deflection">deflection</a>. See <a title="Deflection" href="Deflection">Deflection</a>. 
</p>
<p id="l3">
'Flex<em> also refers to the ability of any material or substance—such as a printing <a title="Substrate" href="Substrate">substrate</a>—to be bent. 
</p>
<p id="l5">
[A means of automatically suppressing small details such as cupped serifs that would print poorly at small sizes. At large sizes or high resolutions, the details are automatically reinstated.] 
</p>
